Description

This lab contains a path traversal vulnerability in the functionality used to display product images. The application does not properly validate user input, allowing access to files outside the intended directory.

Objective

Retrieve the contents of the /etc/passwd file.

Steps to Solve
Intercept the request using Burp Suite while loading a product image.
Identify the parameter responsible for fetching the image (e.g., filename).

Modify the filename parameter to:

../../../etc/passwd
Send the modified request to the server.
Observe the response containing the contents of the /etc/passwd file.
Conclusion

The vulnerability occurs due to improper input validation, allowing directory traversal and unauthorized access to sensitive system files.
